[4] Cuba: NOT
Date: Thu 15 May 2014
Source: Medicina Cubana blog [in Spanish, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
http://medicinacubana.blogspot.be/2014/05/esta-presente-en-cuba-la-enfermedad.html


An independent journalist issued a report (http://www.miscelaneasdecuba.net/web/Article/Index/53747f643a682e0eb058aaa8#.U3ouJq5Vgxd in Spanish), allegedly from the Cuban Ministry of Public Health, that chikungunya virus infections were occurring in Cuba. This same report indicated that there were cases and deaths due to ebolavirus infection in Cuba. In a follow up report cited above, Dr EA Gonzales officially refuted the report that these viruses were present in Cuba and responsible for human cases.

--
communicated by:
Roland Hubner
Superior Health Council
Brussels
Belgium
<roland.hubner@sante.belgique.be>

[Normally, ProMED-mail would not post a report as inaccurate as the one above on chikungunya and ebolaviruses in Cuba. Because it is an example of how inaccurate and irresponsible reporting runs the risk of causing unnecessary public panic, it is included in this week's update. The refutation of the original report by Dr Gonzales is an example of timely presentation of sound, scientifically based information correcting the original misinformation.

Maps of Cuba can be accessed at http://www.caribseek.com/Caribbean_Maps/images/cuba800.gif and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2482881,20. - Mod.TY]

