[Concerning the Dominican Republic, interestingly, the 14 May 2014 edition of El Viajero (http://www.elviajero.com.do/la-chikungunya-se-extiende-en-20-provincias-del-pais/ in Spanish) indicated that the vice minister of public health, Rafael Schiffino, reported that there were now cases of chikungunya virus infection in 20 of the country's 23 provinces. San Cristobal continues to be the province most affected. No case numbers were given.

A map showing the counties and territories with autochthonous transmission of chikungunya in the Americas, as of 6 May 2014, can be seen at http://www.paho.org/hq/images/stories/AD/HSD/IR/Viral_Diseases/Chikungunya/CHIKV-Data-Caribe-2014-May-06.jpg. - Mod.TY]

